#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/sonypi.rst:129
msgid "Bugs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/sonypi.rst:131
msgid ""
"several users reported that this driver disables the BIOS-managed Fn-keys "
"which put the laptop in sleeping state, or switch the external monitor on/"
"off. There is no workaround yet, since this driver disables all APM "
"management for those keys, by enabling the ACPI management (and the ACPI "
"core stuff is not complete yet). If you have one of those laptops with "
"working Fn keys and want to continue to use them, don't use this driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/sonypi.rst:139
msgid ""
"some users reported that the laptop speed is lower (dhrystone tested) when "
"using the driver with the fnkeyinit parameter. I cannot reproduce it on my "
"laptop and not all users have this problem. This happens because the "
"fnkeyinit parameter enables the ACPI mode (but without additional ACPI "
"control, like processor speed handling etc). Use ACPI instead of APM if it "
"works on your laptop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/sonypi.rst:147
msgid ""
"sonypi lacks the ability to distinguish between certain key events on some "
"models."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/sonypi.rst:150
msgid ""
"some models with the nvidia card (geforce go 6200 tc) uses a different way "
"to adjust the backlighting of the screen. There is a userspace utility to "
"adjust the brightness on those models, which can be downloaded from https://"
"www.acc.umu.se/~erikw/program/smartdimmer-0.1.tar.bz2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/laptops/sonypi.rst:156
msgid ""
"since all development was done by reverse engineering, there is *absolutely "
"no guarantee* that this driver will not crash your laptop. Permanently."
msgstr ""
